{
  "stem": "24212.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I go to pay, and there is the same gal who was there before the war, Maria, or whatever her name was.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said very casually, paying my bill, well Mary, where were you during the war?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she said to me, right here, dearie, right here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, thank God.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I wouldn't switch with her, with Auschwitz, with everything else, I wouldn't switch with her.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Five years or more, she sat on that orange crate, or what, so her feet wouldn't get cold, saying, 2.50, thank you very much, come again. 3.50, thank you very much, come again.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it all depends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somebody would be very unhappy with my life and happy with Mary's life, saying, 2.50 thank you very much, come again, in the milk bar.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, the meaning of life, or the purpose of life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What did they give you to eat in Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at one point, at the lowest point in Auschwitz-- not in the other camp-- somebody said, somebody in the know said, 890 calories a day, which is very hard to believe until you will hear what it was.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the morning a liquid, brownish in color, that came sometimes under the title of coffee, sometimes under the title of tea, but it was always the same damn thing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And very seldom was it warm.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was supposed to be warm, but by the time they brought it, I don't know, half a mile from the kitchen-- in huge cauldrons, two and two women had to bring it-- that's it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then came lunch.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We got a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know how many ounces, but it was like a slice of-- the size only, size of a slice of American bread.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
